"pdf_methodology_body" =
"Latency is measured as the round-trip time (RTT), in milliseconds, for each successful network request.\n\n\
Jitter is calculated as the sample standard deviation of RTT values from successful responses, representing latency variability over time. When the set contains 20 or more samples, the top 5%% and bottom 5%% values are discarded to reduce the impact of isolated outliers.\n\n\
Packet loss represents the percentage of network requests that failed relative to the total number of attempts.\n\n\
All calculations are performed locally on the device, without relying on external servers.";

